dling unexpected events. Yet arrogance, a hot temper, and relatively weak leadership could undermine crew cohesion and command effectiveness.\nBalancing the selection criteria (reliability, technical and cognitive competence, calm judgment under pressure, sound decision\u2011making, teamwork/communication, and long\u2011term suitability), **Candidate\u202fB** offers the most well\u2011rounded profile for a long\u2011distance pilot given the current evidence. While his interpersonal issues should be monitored, they do not outweigh his strong technical skills, stress tolerance, and conscientiousness.\n**Vote:** Candidate\u202fB\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_1\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}", "thoughts": "We need to produce final answer as per instructions: PUBLIC_MESSAGE and METADATA_JSON. We are agent_1. We have already responded earlier with a vote for Candidate B. Now we need to handle the request: \"Handle the requests as specified in the System Instruction.\" The system instruction says we are to discuss and vote. The user asks to handle the requests as specified. Likely they want us to produce the public message and metadata. We need to incorporate any new info? The discussion so far: multiple agents have answered the question about missing info. Now we need to continue discussion. We should provide our reasoning, maybe ask further questions if any missing info. We have already asked about reliability of A and strengths of D, got no info. So we have no new info. We can now state our vote. We should also note uncertainties. According to guidelines, we should consider all candidates and weigh strengths/weaknesses. We can reaffirm vote for Candidate B. Provide reasoning. Then output metadata.\n\nThus produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE summarizing reasoning and vote. METADATA_JSON with vote Candidate B."}
